Lakeshore

A gently lapping lake,  
Under the wide sky’s eye,  
Mirrors the clouds drifting,  
With a tender sigh.  

Birds swoop in gladness,  
Over the cerulean blue,  
While the breeze carries whispers,  
In a circuit so true.  


- Amy Lowell
